  <span id="freeText7598387773173790638" style="display:none">When I first started reading Orhan Pamuk's books I really struggled<br />and ended up abandoning Snow and My Name Is Read!!!!!!!<br />It just seemed to complex and I couldn't follow at all really.<br /><br />But after reading Museum Of Innocence I really enjoyed this book<br />and started to feel I was understanding this great writers work.<br /><br />Now I have finished Silent House....which I really loved!<br />Now I really do want to go back and read his books that i have abandoned.<br />Silent House just captivated me!The characters were really interesting<br />and each chapter was in the voice of a different character.<br /><br />At the end of I wanted to know even more about Turkey and Istanbul<br />and I think reading Organs books is a great way to do that!<br /><br />I will go back and read Snow and My Name Is Red and his other works<br />with no fear of abandoning them..Lol<br /><br />Also I really need to visit Istanbul soon!!!</span>
