  <span id="freeText18168151692419333188" style="display:none">Sleepless nights are what this novel granted me - thank you very much, Orhan Pamuk! <br />Not to be misunderstood: This is a masterpiece dealing with family drama in which Pamuk has yet again proved his exceptional, structured and picturesque writing style. <br /><br />The novel blatantly exposes us to political and religious differences spanning over decades in a family and its surrounding in a transformational culture &amp; country. <br /><br />This story has a huge impact on me for many reasons, but was it a coincidence that one of the main characters has the same name as I do and also read the novel ‘Fathers and Sons’ by Iwan Turgenew? <br />Was it necessary for this very same character to die by the evil hands of a fascist guy at a time when I coincidentally ran into a quite difficult situation myself with this novel in my hands? 😳<br />Creepy! It still gives me the chills when I remember that incident. <br /><br />Yes yes...it all must have been “just” a coincidence, I (want to) believe and hope for all the better &amp; utmost peaceful change management procedures in transformational cultures across the globe. <br /><br />A fierce recommendation regardless of any personal experiences ☺️ <br /><br />#peace ✌️ #love ❤️ #appreciation 🙏</span>
